        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 28 at 12:40AM CDT by NWS Dodge City KS</headline>
        <description>At 1240 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 8 miles south of Johnson City to near
Richfield. Movement was southeast at 35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Strong thunderstorms will be near...
Richfield around 1245 AM CDT.
Rolla around 1255 AM CDT.

Other locations in the path of these storms include Feterita and
Hugoton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
